tweet: Happy Halloween to all the trick-or-treaters! Have fun all across #MN06, but especially @CityofAnoka, the Halloween Capital of the world!

Enjoyed meeting with @BetsyDeVosED to discuss Education Freedom Scholarships. I am a proud co-sponsor of H.R.1434 because this tax credit provides states more latitude to select education that fits their needs and supports scholarships that would address our #skillsgap! pic.twitter.com/bfkynATSJU

October serves as #DomesticViolenceAwarenessMonth. These heinous crimes account for 15% of all violent crimes. If you or someone you know needs help, call or chat @ndvh 24/7, 365 at 1-800-799-7233 #endDV #DVAM2019

Congrats to the @cityofotsegomn! Huge thanks to the City Council and Mayor Stockamp for their tireless efforts to ensure traveling in #MN06 is both safe and efficient. Loved joining @the_USO with my wife Jacquie today to put care packages together for our service members abroad! With two of our sons currently serving, this opportunity means the world to us - to be able to send a connection from home to our nation’s heroes! #BeTheForce pic.twitter.com/JufpCCbtBs

Today, I am wearing my pink ribbon in honor of #BreastCancerAwareness. I lost my sister Bridget to this unforgiving disease and I carry her memory with me every day as I raise awareness and support for other families affected. We must keep fighting to find a cure. pic.twitter.com/Bnd95pZjkg

Visited the Philips ATLAS wall display on the Hill today. This initiative by @DeptVetAffairs will increase access to telemedicine. They will be installed in @AmericanLegion’s and @VFWHQ’s in order to make health services available to our nation's heroes in rural areas! pic.twitter.com/JxKevnqfKW

Every Tuesday, I send out my weekly newsletter to keep #MN06 up to date on what’s happening in Washington. To view past newsletters and to subscribe to receive future newsletters, visit my website here:  https://emmer.house.gov/newsletters

Due to the hard work and bravery of our nation’s first responders, America is a safer place. On #NationalFirstRespondersDay, I want to thank all of the men and women who go above and beyond to serve their communities and keep them safe.

I am grateful to our armed forces and @realDonaldTrump for their continued mission to fight terrorism. Nothing can outmatch the United States military. Those who wish to support terrorism should be prepared to face relentless pursuit.

I visited @DEAHQ on Capitol Hill as they raised awareness for #NationalTakeBackDay. Prescription drug abuse is dangerous and returning unused drugs to a safe drop off-site is very important. Find a location near you today by visiting  https://takebackday.dea.gov  pic.twitter.com/4LAumjB7iv

Pleased to see @realDonaldTrump‘s support for mining in Minnesota! I look forward to continuing our work together to responsibly mine critical minerals and bring jobs and economic prosperity to everyone in our great state.
